{
  "texts": [
    "Supervised learning is usually integrated with unsupervised learning to solve practical problems.",
    "Reinforcement learning utilizes iterative learning to train the agent to react to the environment, thus achieving optimal results by finding a balance between exploration and exploitation.",
    "As representatives of reinforcement learning, Bayesian Optimization (BO), Markov decision process and Q-learning are typical algorithms for experimental design and closed-loop optimization for problems with multiarray parameters.",
    "Table 1 summarizes the mainstream ML algorithms and the suitable model evaluation parameters.",
    "It is worth noting that state-of-the-art neural network architectures, including Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks and Transformers can be applied across supervised, unsupervised, and reinforcement learning to enable diverse applications such as property prediction, structure optimization, and generative design in materials science."
